Madam President, I should like to share a cause of great satisfaction with you all. A great social and economic pact has recently been signed between the government, union leaders and business leaders in Spain. This agreement establishes Spain as a country capable of joining forces to overcome its difficulties, face up to its challenges and reinforce the welfare state. Ladies and gentlemen, in this global crisis, this agreement is a unique example of how, by society as a whole taking responsibility, we are making agreements with the idea of winning the future and building a strong Spain in a Union that plays an increasingly important role.